abstract: How Ben Rhodes rewrote the rules of diplomacy for the digital age.
snippet: How Ben Rhodes rewrote the rules of diplomacy for the digital age.
lead_paragraph: Picture him as a young man, standing on the waterfront in North Williamsburg, at a polling site, on Sept. 11, 2001, which was Election Day in New York City. He saw the planes hit the towers, an unforgettable moment of sheer disbelief followed by panic and shock and lasting horror, a scene that eerily reminded him, in the aftermath, of the cover of the Don DeLillo novel “Underworld.”

abstract: Backers of the law say it will accelerate similar efforts elsewhere. Hawaii is the only other state to have raised the smoking age.
snippet: Backers of the law say it will accelerate similar efforts elsewhere. Hawaii is the only other state to have raised the smoking age.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — California will become the second state in the nation to raise the smoking age to 21 and will begin regulating electronic cigarettes like other tobacco products under legislation signed by Gov. Jerry Brown on Wednesday.

abstract: The 2017 model addresses problems with steering, road noise and a lack of structure in its 2016 counterpart.
snippet: The 2017 model addresses problems with steering, road noise and a lack of structure in its 2016 counterpart.
lead_paragraph: AROUND six years ago, Hyundai figured a 10-year warranty was not enough to attract shoppers and conjured up daring design for more attention. Sonata was the first to get the Fluidic Sculpture makeover, but the fifth-generation Elantra ended up being the swoopiest of the fleet. Hyundai’s newest gamble? Toning down those curves.
headline_main: Video Review: Hyundai Elantra Offers Fewer Curves, but a Better Ride
headline_print_headline: Elantra Offers Fewer Curves, but Better Ride

abstract: Thomas F. Steyer and his political advocacy group, NextGen Climate, will target at least 203 college and university campuses in seven mostly battleground states.
snippet: Thomas F. Steyer and his political advocacy group, NextGen Climate, will target at least 203 college and university campuses in seven mostly battleground states.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The billionaire environmentalist Thomas F. Steyer and his political advocacy group, NextGen Climate, will spend at least $25 million on a get-out-the-vote campaign targeting young voters this year in seven mostly battleground states, the group announced on Monday.

abstract: With the coming of her new film, “Money Monster,” Ms. Foster talks about privacy, the desperation to communicate and her ceaseless self-examination.
snippet: With the coming of her new film, “Money Monster,” Ms. Foster talks about privacy, the desperation to communicate and her ceaseless self-examination.
lead_paragraph: CULVER CITY, Calif. — Because of the political moment in which it’s landing, the new movie “Money Monster” — about a cheesy TV financial guru and the viewer who takes him hostage — will almost surely be seen as a parable of income inequality and a rigged economy. Which, in large part, it is.

abstract: Over two days at this year’s Mudfest in the Pacific Northwest, 26 journalists evaluated 27 vehicles, including crossovers, S.U.V.s and pickups.
snippet: Over two days at this year’s Mudfest in the Pacific Northwest, 26 journalists evaluated 27 vehicles, including crossovers, S.U.V.s and pickups.
lead_paragraph: Thinking about buying a sport utility vehicle or crossover? Get in line. According to IHS Automotive, the segment outsold sedans in the United States last year. Now, you could buy a station wagon (they handle more like sports sedans because of their lower center of gravity) or a minivan, but buyers have voted for crossovers with their checkbooks. Cheap gas helps.
